#. module: software_reseller
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:software_reseller.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"From the <strong><font class=\"text-o-color-1\">Licenses App</font></"
"strong>, specially tailored for the Software reseller industry, you an have "
"an overview of all your software licenses. Click on one specific license to "
"track license\n"
"            keys belonging to each customer."
msgstr ""
"通过专为软件分销行业定制开发的<strong><font class=\"text-o-color-1\">授权管理"
"应用</font></strong>，您可查看企业所有软件授权的整体概况。点击任意一项具体授"
"权，即可追踪每位客户对应的授权密钥信息。"

#. module: software_reseller
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:software_reseller.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"From the <strong><font class=\"text-o-color-1\">Planning App</font></"
"strong>, click New:"
msgstr ""
"在<strong><font class=\"text-o-color-1\">排期管理应用</font></strong>中，点击"
"新建按钮操作如下："

#. module: software_reseller
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:software_reseller.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"From the <strong><font class=\"text-o-color-1\">Timesheet App</font></"
"strong>, or on one task, consultants and developers can timesheet their "
"spent time on the different phases of the project: Business Need Analysis, "
"Odoo\n"
"            Configuration, or Training &amp; Support. This will be reflected "
"as \"Delivered Quantity\" on the sale order lines."
msgstr ""
"顾问与开发人员可通过<strong><font class=\"text-o-color-1\">工时单应用</"
"font></strong>，或直接在对应任务中，记录自身在项目各阶段的工作时长，涵盖业务"
"需求分析、Odoo 系统配置、培训与技术支持等环节。该工时数据将同步体现在销售订单"
"行的实际交付量字段中。"

#. module: software_reseller
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:software_reseller.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"From the Product Sales tab, you can also add development serves in one click "
"as Optional Products."
msgstr "在产品销售标签页中，您也可一键添加开发服务，并将其设为选配产品。"

#. module: software_reseller
#: model_terms:ir.ui.view,arch_db:software_reseller.welcome_article_body
msgid ""
"From the subscription, using the top buttons, jump to the purchase order to "
"buy these licenses to Oracle. You can send by email your request for "
"quotation, then confirm the order. At that point, Oracle will send you the "
